title: Project manager and technical specialist - Nordea access review pilot using SailPoint Identity IQ
description: A Nordea group wide automated solution was needed to ensure compliance with Nordea company policies regarding access rights. In this pilot, PSK used his experience from former projects together with the existing SailPoint identity and access management project and an external vendor to produce a access certification review. The pilot was a success and received many gratulations from upper management.

title: Remedy upgrade test case project manager
description: The Remedy service management tool needed an upgraded to the newest version without jeopardizing the day-to-day work. Two project streams were created – installation/data migration and test case. PSK created the project plan targeting not only the known processes, but also indirect tools/solutions that the processes depended on. The process owners received training in test cases creation and a small SharePoint site was created to keep track of all test cases. PSK realized the need for test cases to be used more actively in the future day-to-day work when a new change is introduced to Remedy. Thus, a new process between requesters of Remedy changes and the Remedy technical team was agreed.

title: License management proof of concept
description: Management wants a higher degree of automation in software license reporting. The scope for this project was to find/develop the “glue” that would enable current tools to exchange the data needed for license management. Using experience from other companies, three solutions was found and the chosen solution was implemented in a proof of concept environment. A management report was created to outline what was possible to gain in the SW license area as well as in the SACM area. Tools used: BMC Remedy, Microsoft SCCM, Seamless Technologies, ISO-19770.

title: Analysis, design, education and implementation of the security compliance profile tool.
description: The development department wanted to demonstrate their compliance towards the Nordea Security policies covering their area. PSK located the relevant policies and developed a tool for each team to enter compliance status for their area. The tool was approved by the security and compliance department and PSK educated team leaders in policies and the associated compliance work, to kick-off the tool. The tool gave management an easy colourised view of any trouble areas, but even better was the awareness about compliance, which was brought to attention when teams applied the tool.

title: Analyst and advisor for the segregation of duties project.
description: Management wanted even further segregation of duties between the infrastructure and the development department. description: • Responsible for multiple targets of very high strategic interest to the United States. • Performed background research on collection issues, performs collection gaps analysis, brings together the appropriate organizations to develop collection solutions, and helps formulate the overall strategy. • Selected to team with a government lead to develop a Deep Dive for a high-priority target. title: Technician II Network Operation Day Shift Lead
description: Managed a team of 14 to 17 technicians in day to day operations in the South NOC for T-Mobile. I motivated and lead the DDS team to complete network goals and assist in the individual growth of team members in the skill needed in the DDS role. I prioritized and escalated all issues internally and externally sourced. Verified circuit delivery on wireless voice and data networks thru multiple transmission mediums RFC tested and turned up cell sites while documenting all procedures to enhance and speed up the time required to turn up a cell site, while eliminating duplicated work orders and effort Used programs such as: Homer, Citrix, Granite, ALU SAM 5620, NetExpert, PuTTY manager, Insite, Microsoft Outlook, Excel, including experience with pivot tables, Word, Sliped, IPControl Daily Processing up to 1,400 work orders, trouble tickets as well as creating trouble tickets and tasks when needed for alarmed cell sites, or contacted switch operators and field technicians to troubleshoot the alarm Programmed, tested, troubleshoot, provisioned, pushed operating system firmware upgrades, verified configurations, checked alarm functions monitoring, and supported multiple devices including, ALU 7705 and 7750 routers, Cisco 7609 routers, JDSU Collector, MSO and site NID's, and JDSU QT600 test heads Utilized the CLI and/or the GUI to configure and test ALU 7705, 7750's and JDSU NID's Contacted vendors and equipment manufactures to create trouble tickets for repair of sites, equipment, VLAN's and cabling Troubleshoot problems with devices, connections, VLAN's, broadcast storms, vendors or other service or none-service impacting situations Trained NOC personnel in live site reprovisioning of cell site NIDs Assisted Field techs in restoring 2G & 3G service to cell sites Experienced in troubleshooting microwave, COW, and COLT cell sites for high priority events
